.TH SENDMSG(1),User Commands,SENDMSG(1)

.SH NAME
sendmsg - send a message on a general hook

.SH SYNOPSIS
sendmsg -h hook [-c byte]... [-s string]...

.SH DESCRIPTION
sendmsg assembles a message in an internal buffer from its flag arguments and then sends the resulting bytes on the specified general hook.

Flags are processed left to right.
Each -c and -s appends to the buffer in the order given;
-h chooses the destination hook.
The message is sent once, after all arguments have been processed.

Hook numbers must be in the range 0 through 15 ($00..$0F).

.SH OPTIONS
-h hook: Destination hook number.
Parsed as decimal, or hex with a leading $ or 0x.
Required.

-c byte: Append a single byte to the message buffer.
Parsed the same way as hook numbers.

-s string: Append the NUL-terminated string to the message buffer, including the terminating NUL.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Error: invalid flag "ARG" - an argument did not begin with - or used an unknown letter.

Error: no hook num provided - no -h was given.

Error: invalid hook num $XX - the hook number was 16 or greater.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: Message sent.

1: Invalid flag, missing hook number, or hook number out of range.
